{
  "doc_id": "4843",
  "text": "SJ23B is a jatrophane diterpene derived from the plant Eurphorbia hiberna. Rullas et al. [CITATION_1] planned experiments to determine whether the mechanisms of action of SJ23B are similar to those of phorbol esters, although the novel compound is structurally different from phorbol esters. The phorbol ester prostratin has two effects on the replication cycle of HIV-1: down-regulation of HIV-1 receptors and induction of viral transcription. In PBMCs activated by CD3 + interleukin-2 for 48 h, 2 h of exposure to SJ23B at a concentration of 0.1 or 1 µM down-regulated membrane expression of CD4, CCR5 and CXCR4. SJ23B had little or no effect on receptor expression on resting PBMCs.",
